        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <head>200. Letter From <persName corresp="#p_NHC_1">Helen Cohn Needham</persName> to
                    the Deputy Under Secretary of State for Management (<persName corresp="#p_RBH_1">Read</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d200fn1">Source: National
                        Archives, RG 59, Records of the Under Secretary for Management (M),
                        1977–1978, Box 8, Chron February 1978. No classification marking. Copies
                        were sent to <persName corresp="#p_PR_1">Palmer</persName> and King.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1978-01-26">January 26, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RBH_1">Read</persName>:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It has come to our attention that members of the State Department’s personnel
                    staff have been telling women Foreign Service officers that the sex
                    discrimination class actions brought on behalf of women Foreign Service
                        officers<note n="2" xml:id="d200fn2">See <ref target="#d195">Documents
                            195</ref> and <ref target="#d199">199</ref>.</note> are frivolous and
                    without basis and that class members will be ultimately liable for the
                    Department’s attorney fees. In our view these comments constitute harassment and
                    intimidation of the class members and we must insist that official action be
                    taken to prevent further improper comments. We request that you inform in
                    writing all members of your staff, that any remarks to women Foreign Service
                    officers which could be interpreted as intimidation, harassment, or otherwise
                    suggesting that they disassociate themselves from the class-action litigation
                    must be halted immediately.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="strong">Bruce J. Terris</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_NHC_1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Helen Cohn Needham</hi>
                                </persName>
                                <note n="3" xml:id="d200fn3">Only <persName corresp="#p_NHC_1">Needham</persName> signed above these typed
                                    signatures.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
